Real Sweep Impact Analysis and Post-Implementation Testing

The next stage of the sweep impact analysis begins after the implementation and deployment of the BI v3 model in the production environment.

Overview of the Real Sweep Impact Process

	1.	Exposure List and Dataset Preparation:
	•	BI will provide a comprehensive list of exposures intended for processing through the claim exception batch within the CC Production environment.
	•	The goal is to use the full exposure list to calculate the final sweep impact, starting on the deployment date.
	2.	Testing Environment Considerations:
	•	If a production-like environment is not available in the CC Perf region, IT may use a lower environment to simulate and check the process. Alternatively, a nightly batch approach can be adopted, with an initial batch of 1,000 exposures, allowing issues to be identified promptly.
	3.	Batch Processing Strategy:
	•	The sweep can be conducted over multiple nightly batches or within a single day, depending on resources and scheduling needs. Each nightly batch can process between 5,000 and 7,000 exposures, totaling up to 13,500 exposures for the entire sweep.
	•	Ideally, the implementation and sweep should be completed on the same day or at the latest, the first day of the weekend.

Scenario Planning for Implementation

The following table outlines potential scenarios for the sweep implementation, detailing the pros and cons of each approach.

Scenario	Pros	Cons
1) Sunday Implementation	- Allows for full-day completion with no competing processes.- Minimal claim activity.	- Limited availability of resources (e.g., IT, BI teams) over the weekend.
